            PhD Candidate | Geospatial Scientist | Data
            Storyteller
            I am a PhD candidate in sociology at Stanford and will be
            defending my dissertation in August. My research relies upon
            big spatial data and addresses geographic problems such as
            site selection, resource allocation, and geodemographic
            classification. Browse the pages and links on my website to
            learn more about my interests, prior work experience,
            skills, and projects.
